DAMATURU – Preparatory to the forthcoming Eid-El-Kabir Salah celebrations, the Nigeria Security and Civil Defense Corps (NSCDC) says it has deployed 575 personnel across Yobe State ahead of the festive holiday. The Public Relations Officer (PRO) NSCDC Yobe Command, ASC Bala Garba revealed in a press statement made available to Daily Independent in Damaturu today. According to him NSCDC Commandant Saidu Y. Aliyu has deployed 575 personnel ahead of Eid-El-Kabir Sallah celebrations and urged the officers to be extra vigilant on suspicious movements of unidentified persons in the state. “The newly posted State Commandant of Yobe in his preparedness towards ensuring a hitch – free 2022 EID-EL KABIR Sallah celebration addresses officers and men to be vigilant and ensure watertight security coverage in all the 17 Local Government Area of Yobe State. He stressed that, all necessary arrangements has been made to deploy operatives ranging from Operation Department, Rapid Response Squad RRS, Anti vandal squad, Intelligence personnel’s among others prior to the festive period to take care of any eventualities. “The deployment covers all Eid Prayer grounds, recreation centres, Motor parks, Markets and all Critical National Assets to include both public and private investment in the State.” “CC Saidu also call on good people of Yobe State to remain vigilant, and report any suspicious movement to security operatives and wished the Muslim faithful a happy Eid – El Kabir celebration”.